article.headline: Cleveland State 66, Kent State 59
article.story: CLEVELAND (AP) -- Raheem Moss and Carlos English each had 14 points to lead Cleveland State to a 66-59 win over Kent State on Wednesday night. Victor Morris added 11 points for the Vikings (5-3), who shot only 36 percent from the field but went 10-for-22 on 3-pointers to the Golden Flashes' 5-for-17 on 3s. Cleveland State also outrebounded Kent State 43-35. Julian Sullinger led the Golden Flashes with 12 points and eight rebounds. Armon Gates added 11 points and Isaac Knight had 10 for Kent State (4-3). The Vikings were up 34-24 at halftime and led by as much as 16 in the second half. Kent State pulled within four points with just over a minute remaining on an Omni Smith layup, but was outscored 5-2 as the game closed. Cleveland State shot almost 67 percent from the free-throw line. ^
